Kano State Governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, has urged Muslims to continue to cherish the teachings of the Ramadan and exhibit self-discipline, piety, love, unity, peace and support for the weak and less privileged. In his Sallah message, Ganduje in a press statement signed by the state Commissioner for Information, Malam Muhammad Garba, called on Nigerians irrespective of religion, ethnicity or political inclination to always live peacefully and selflessly contribute to the development of Nigeria. The Chief Imam of Al-Furqan mosque, Dr Bashir Aliyu Umar, enjoined Muslims to sustain the good virtues learnt in the Ramadan, the greatest of which, he said, was the fear of Allah. The imam reminded the people on theÂ  economic situation in the country and urged them to sustain their kindness to the poor during the Ramadan.